HEADWORD: Self-partiality
<hw>Self`-par`ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That
partiality to himself by which a man overrates his own worth when
compared with others.</def> <rj><au>Kames.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

